Contest Description
------- -----------

*** contest/formal_contest formal
	About formal contests, including logging in.

*** contest/informal_contest informal
	About informal contests, including logging in.

*** contest/untimed_contest untimed
	About untimed contests, including logging in.

*** common/xterminals local
	How to make windows if you are using an
	xterminal emulator.

*** email/email_unix_tools email not_help_index
	How to use Bourne shell or TCL tools in your own
	personal account.

*** email/sh all email not_help_index
	Bourne shell tools for use in your own personal
	account.

	hpcm_sendmail
	    Send email to the judge.

	hpcm_get
	    Send email to the judge to get files.

	hpcm_extract
	    Extract hpcm_get gotten files from replies.

	hpcm_help
	    Display help files.

	hpcm_sandbox
	    Execute programs with resource limits.

	hpcm_clisp
	    Execute or compile COMMONLISP programs.

	hpcm_submit
	    Send submission file to the judge.

	procmailrc
	    Inclusion for .procmailrc to invoke hpcm_
	    extract automatically to extract files
	    gotten by hpcm_get.
#
# # # # # # # # # *** email/tcl all email not_help_index
#	Tclsh shell tools for email contests.
#	An alternative to Bourne shell.
#
#	hpcm_get
#	    Send email to the judge to get files.
#
#	hpcm_extract
#	    Extract hpcm_get gotten files from replies.

Solving Problems:
-----------------

*** common/solving local
	How to write a solution file, how to test it,
	how to submit it, if you have been given a
	contestant account.

*** email/email_solving email
	How to write a solution file, how to test it,
	how to submit it, if you are using your own
	personal account.

*** common/input common
	Advice on input formats.

*** common/output common
	Advice on output formats.

*** common/print common
	How to print files.

*** common/commonlisp common
	How to write COMMONLISP solutions.


Scores and the Scoreboard:
--------------------------

*** common/scores common
	How to find out your scores, and also how to
	ask questions of the judge.

*** common/scoreboard common
	Interpreting the scoreboard notation.


Advice:
-------

*** common/c++	common
	Special C++ advice.

*** common/java	common
	Special JAVA advice.

*** common/advice common
	Polonic advice on how to select problems and
	find errors.

# end_help_index

# begin_advanced_help

Advice on Specific Kinds of Problems
------ -- -------- ----- -- --------

*** advanced/dynamic_programming	advanced
	Solving dynamic programming problems.

*** advanced/2D_geometry	advanced
	Solving 2D geometry problems.

*** advanced/breadth_first_search	advanced
	Solving problems (e.g. mazes) with breadth first
	search.


Advanced Advice on Specific Kinds of Problems
-------- ------ -- -------- ----- -- --------

*** advanced/constrained_search	very-advanced
	Brute force search with constraints.

*** advanced/network_flows	very-advanced
	Solving network flow problems.

*** advanced/optimal_matchings	very-advanced
	Solving optimal matching problems.

*** advanced/3D_geometry	very-advanced
	Solving 3D geometry problems.

# end_advanced_help
